BELGIUM

The demand for telecommunications equipment in Belgium is stimulated by the
availability of many new and exciting technologies for business and private
telecommunications and the gradual deregulation of the Belgian and other
European telecommunication environments.  The national telephone company is
continuously investing in the digitization and modernization of its network.
The new pan-European networks for ISDN services and paging are gradually being
installed throughout the country.  The pan-European GSM network will be
developed with a private partner during the second half of 1993.  Due to the
fast growth of commercial TV and the increasing use of video for public
relations, the market for broadcasting equipment continues to grow.  However,
there is considerable domestic competition from Alcatel and Siemmens, as well
as other European providers not manufacturing in Belgium.

