COLOMBIA

The prospective award in early 1994 of six licenses to provide cellular
service within three (3) regions in Colombia will radically alter the domestic
and international telecommunications landscape, bypassing the developmental
stage of hard-wired phones.

If TV broadcasting is privatized, there will be a new demand for equipment due
to creation of new TV stations.  The Bogota Telephone Company (ETB), along
with TELEBOGOTA, hopes to initiate transmission of regional Colombian TV
channels using equipment and studio space of INRAVISION, the Colombian agency
in charge of broadcasting.

New advances in satellite technology, fiber optics and other options, are
spawning a new generation of satellites, giving more power to those already in
orbit.  With stronger TV signals beamed throughout the Southern Hemisphere,
the satellite dish size will be reduced and demand increased.

