EGYPT

The current telephone density of three units per 100 persons is planned to
increase to seven units per 100 by the year 2010.  This will require the
installation of 250,000 lines per year.  The Government of Egypt has allocated
US$ 700 million in the current five year plan (1992-1997) including US$ 200
million from USAID.  In 1993 USAID is providing US$ 30 million for
