TURKEY

By the end of 1993, telephone switch capacity is expected to reach 10.5
million lines.  The largest end-user of telecommunications equipment is the
Turkish PTT, which has a monopoly in telecommunications services.  Currently,
the Turkish Government is discussing privatization of some services.
